File: Former IPID head Robert McBride is competing for the job against 27 other candidates. JOHANNESBURG - Former Independent Police Investigative Directorate (IPID) head Robert McBride is in the running to become Deputy Public Protector. Mcbride is competing for the job against 27 other candidates, among them is Buang Jones from the SA Human Rights Commission. READ: Robert McBride details capture of judicial agencies In his tenure as Ipid head, McBride faced numerous suspensions. Members of the public have until 16 October to comment on the suitability of candidates. The appointed candidate will take over from Kevin Malunga.